{%- doc -%}
  Inline pill badge for a menu link (e.g. red "SALE" next to a
  "Deals" item). Resolves badge by case-insensitive title match
  against `menu_link_badge` blocks declared in the header section
  schema.

  Required to satisfy REJ-SEC-002: `link.title` MUST be `| escape`d
  on render — that prevented merchants from baking raw `<span>`
  HTML into the linklist title to get a visual badge. This block-
  driven escape-safe alternative gives them the same visual without
  punching a hole in the XSS guard.

  Multiple matches: if two badge blocks both match a link's title,
  the first one in block order wins. The `{%- break -%}` enforces
  this so a merchant who duplicates a configuration sees a stable,
  predictable result rather than a doubled-up pill.

  @param {link} link        - the linklist link being rendered
  @param {section} section  - the header section (for blocks lookup)
{%- enddoc -%}
{%- if section.blocks.size > 0 -%}
  {%- assign link_title_lower = link.title | downcase | strip -%}
  {%- for badge_block in section.blocks -%}
    {%- if badge_block.type == 'menu_link_badge' and badge_block.settings.link_text != blank -%}
      {%- assign target_lower = badge_block.settings.link_text | downcase | strip -%}
      {%- if target_lower == link_title_lower -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Inline `style` attribute carries merchant-picked colors.
          Falls back to red bg / white fg if the picker was cleared.
          The `| escape` filter on `badge_text` keeps user input out
          of the HTML stream — same reason `link.title` is escaped.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <span
          class="kt-header__menu-badge"
          style="background-color: {{ badge_block.settings.badge_bg | default: '#dc2626' }}; color: {{ badge_block.settings.badge_fg | default: '#ffffff' }};"
          {{ badge_block.shopify_attributes }}
        >{{ badge_block.settings.badge_text | default: 'SALE' | escape }}</span>
        {%- break -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}
